            <thetext>Attached is a snippet with a simple tree, a root node and a sub node.
Follow these steps to reproduce the bug:
* Expand the root node
=&gt; you see the sub node
* Collapse the root node
=&gt; sub node is hidden
* click the button
=&gt; sub node (not visible) is removed from the tree and a new subnode is added
* expand the root node again
=&gt; it seems both subnodes are still in the DOM and are shown both

Reproduced in FF/Opera on Linux. FF/IE on Windows</thetext>
